===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[talken#Middle English|talken, talkien]]'' "to speak with, converse", freq. of {{enm}} ''[[talen#Middle English|talen, talien]]'' "to speak, recount" from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[talian#Old English|talian]]'' "to give an account, reckon" + ''[[-k#Middle English|-k]]'' suffix (cf. ''hark'' from ''hear''; ''stalk'' from ''steal'', ''walk'' from {{ang}} ''[[weallian#Old English|weallian]]'' "to travel, go abroad, wander") from {{proto|Germanic|taljanan|to give account, reckon, tell|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|frs|-}} ''[[talken#Frisian|talken]]'' "to chat", {{etyl|nds|-}} ''[[talk#Low German|talk]]'' (noun) "talk", {{etyl|deu|-}} dialectal ''[[talken#German|talken]]'' "to chatter, mumble", {{ang}} ''[[talu#Old English|talu]]'' "story, statement, recollection". More at [[tale]]

